[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[em 
			""The game-play needs to standout from non-assisted play, and must not be seen as trivial. Note that a game is considered trivial until proven otherwise. If 
			[b 
				"getting perfect times everywhere is not challenging
			]b
			", such a game is considered trivial. If later a technique is found that makes TASing it challenging, that game becomes acceptable."
		]em
